      "content": "Grapefruit juice is a known inhibitor of certain enzymes, which can interact with atorvastatin. This interaction can cause your body to absorb a much higher concentration of the statin than intended, potentially leading to serious side effects. To be safe, you should avoid mixing grapefruit juice with atorvastatin altogether. If you want to keep your routine, try opting for a different juice instead.",
